description:
In 1902, a fire would strike the Review and Herald in Battle Creek, Michigan. It was unquenchable and completely destroyed the printing press. Whilst investigating, it was found that the cause of the fire was linked with Dr. Kellogg and his apostasy. The Kellogg crisis would test the church in its early years and provided a real challenge to the leadership at the time. Unfortunately, Kellogg would go his own way and build his own Sanitarium, once so prosperous would eventually fade in significance.

To find out more about  the 1902 Sanitarium fire visit our website to read our extended article.
